Click the heading to find all pages related to [[Frame]]s in Emacs.

* DoReMi -- incrementally adjust or set frame properties using the arrow keys; return to previous frame configurations (undo)
* FisheyeWithThumbs -- thumbnail frames: a fisheye view of your frames and an alternative to iconifying
* FramesAndRegisters -- saving and restoring a configuration of frames
* FrameConfig -- save and restore some basic frame properties
* FrameModes -- frame commands, including commands to move, iconify/restore, tile, maximize, and resize (e.g. zoom) frames
** <tt>[[frame-cmds.el]]</tt>, <tt>[[zoom-frm.el]]</tt>
** [[Shrink-Wrapping Frames]] -- fit a frame to its displayed buffer
** [[OneOnOneEmacs]] -- frame-friendly Emacs
* FrameMove -- move between frames (i.e., change the input focus) using the arrow keys 
* FrameParameters -- what frame parameters are, and how to set and save them
* FacesPerFrame -- varying faces or themes by frame
* FrameResize -- keeping a constant character width when the frame is resized
* FrameSize -- set the size of frames
* FrameTag -- switch between frames using M-1 to M-9.
* FrameTitle -- change the title of a frame
* OneOnOneEmacs -- making Emacs more frame-oriented, and less (Emacs-)window oriented

